{"text": " This fruit tastes like a mixture of banana, mango, and pineapple. It's known as monstera delicioso fruit and comes from a popular house plant often referred to as the Swiss cheese plant, but not many people realize that it actually produces edible fruit. You know these fruits are ready to pick when they're nice and full in size and the scales have started to slightly spread apart. Then you just wanna set them cut side up into a glass and wait until the scales start to loosen up. When the fruit is ripe and ready to be enjoyed, you should be able to lightly tap on it or flick them with your finger and they should fall right off. It's really important to let these fruits ripen on their own and not to pry off the scales because if you eat the unripe fruit, it can actually burn your mouth. Underneath the scales, you'll see that the ripe fruit actually comes apart in individual segments that perfectly line up with the scales. It is a really unique fruit and the aroma of it smells just like a fragrant pineapple. And the flavor in my opinion is like you combine banana, mango, and pineapple all in one fruit. It's really good. Unlike a lot of other fruits, these tend to ripen in sections rather than the entire fruit ripening at once. So each day as the scales fall off, you get to enjoy a little bit more of it. Let me know down in the comments if you'd give this fruit a try. And until next time, get outside and see what you can find.", "segments": [{"id": 0, "seek": 0, "start": 0.0, "end": 3.16, "text": " This fruit tastes like a mixture of banana, mango, and pineapple.", "tokens": [50364, 639, 6773, 8666, 411, 257, 9925, 295, 14194, 11, 23481, 11, 293, 25740, 13, 50522], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12982994677072549, "compression_ratio": 1.7465564738292012, "no_speech_prob": 0.003515210933983326}, {"id": 1, "seek": 0, "start": 3.16, "end": 5.24, "text": " It's known as monstera delicioso fruit", "tokens": [50522, 467, 311, 2570, 382, 1108, 372, 1663, 1103